{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/joseverareyes/conectar-postgresql-desde-r-crear-y-consultar?scriptVersionId=96128793\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","outputs":[],"execution_count":0},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"75e44a52","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.002282,"end_time":"2022-05-20T14:28:00.185565","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-05-20T14:28:00.183283","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Consultar y crear tablas desde R en Postgrest\n","\n","Crear tablas desde R en motor de base de postgrest, MySQL y SQL es fácil con algunas lineas de sentencias.\n","\n","### 1. Cargamos las librerias\n","\n","```library(DBI)```\n","```library(RODBC)```\n","\n","### 2. Creamos la Conexión \n","\n","#### Para ProstgreSQL\n","\n","```library(RPostgres)```\n","```library(RPostgreSQL)```\n","\n","Es necesario instalar este librería, para complemento de la ```library(DBI)``` para el uso de una database en Postgresql. En algunas versiones de R cran ya no esta la ```library(RPostgres)```\n","\n","```r \n","if(!'RPostgres' %in% installed.packages()){install.packages(\"RPostgres\")}\n","```\n","\n","```r \n","con <- dbConnect(RPostgres::Postgres(), user=\"xxx\",\n","                 password=\"xxx\",\n","                 dbname=\"xxxx\",\n","                 port=5432,\n","                 host=\"xxxx\")\n","```\n","#### Para MySQL\n","\n","```library(RMySQL)```\n","\n","```r \n","con <- dbConnect(MySQL(), user=\"xxx\",\n","                 password=\"xxx\",\n","                 dbname=\"xxxx\",\n","                 host=\"xxxx\")\n","```\n","#### Para SQL\n","\n","```library(RSQLite)```\n","\n","Para esta base de datos es necesario instalar el ODBC de sql [Download Microsoft® ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server® - Windows, Linux y macOS from Official Microsoft Download Center](https://www.microsoft.com/es-es/download/details.aspx?id=56567)\n","\n","```r \n","con <- dbConnect(odbc::odbc(), Driver = \"ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server\",, user=\"xxx\",\n","                 password=\"xxx\",\n","                 dbname=\"xxxx\",\n","                 port=1433,\n","                 host=\"xxxx\")\n","```\n","\n","#### 2.1. Definir Schema?\n","\n","En caso de que queramos definir el schema del database. Por lo general cuando no se define el schema, toma .dbo por default.\n","\n","```r \n","Shema <- DBI::Id(schema = \"prc\", table = \"name_table\")\n","```\n","\n","### 3. Creamos una tabla\n","\n","```r \n","df <- DBI::dbWriteTable(con, Shema, df)\n","```\n","\n","### 4. Creamos una consulta\n","\n","```r \n","df <- DBI::dbGetQuery(con, \"select * from schema.table\")\n","```\n","\n","### 5. Actualizamos una tabla\n","\n","```r \n","df <- DBI::dbAppendTable(con, Shema, df)\n","```\n","\n","Este caso yo lo aplico en SQL y PostgrestSQL\n","\n","#### 5.1. En MySQL?\n","\n","Para este caso es distinto, yo uso este script.\n","\n","```r \n","dbWriteTable(con, \"name_tabledatabase\", df, append = TRUE, row.names = FALSE)\n","```\n","\n","### 6. Cerramos la Conexión\n","\n","```r \n","dbDisconnect(con)\n","```\n","\n","> Para mas detalle puedes consultar : [R Database Interface • DBI (r-dbi.org)](https://dbi.r-dbi.org/)"]}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"R","language":"R","name":"ir"},"language_info":{"codemirror_mode":"r","file_extension":".r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","name":"R","pygments_lexer":"r","version":"4.0.5"},"papermill":{"default_parameters":{},"duration":3.834943,"end_time":"2022-05-20T14:28:00.308709","environment_variables":{},"exception":null,"input_path":"__notebook__.ipynb","output_path":"__notebook__.ipynb","parameters":{},"start_time":"2022-05-20T14:27:56.473766","version":"2.3.4"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}